caption: A lovely square - garden area, with plenty of seating, for a well deserved rest, the Fontaine Dejean is its centre piece, during our visit there was a flea-market in full swing.
Busy.. and a bit noisy ....plus, there's Tramway construction EVERYWHERE...so use the underground pedestrian passage and double-check your bus stops...everything is in constant flux.

Small tree-lined square located in a fairly noisy environment. The square at Place Pasdeloup is located along Boulevard des Filles du Calvaire, opposite the Cirque d’Hiver. It is composed of a large central avenue lined with plane trees. At its center is an elegant stone fountain erected in 1906, topped with a statue of a swan grooming itself.
This square doesn't have many benches to sit on and half of them are occupied by homeless people, which doesn't make you want to come back.
Located in a very quiet area, this square, which faces the Bouglione winter cirque, is unfortunately not very busy.
No, they removed the ping pong table even though it was one of the only ones available 24 hours a day.
Bad encounters, place not very well attended
Nice and quiet for a city center
